udy in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/information-about-house-cleaning-and-expenses-in-turkey.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/information-about-house-cleaning-and-expenses-in-turkey.webp","width":"1168","height":"880","caption":"House cleaning services cost and tips Turkey","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/house-cleaning-and-expenses-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/house-cleaning-and-expenses-in-turkey/","name":"Information About House Cleaning and Expenses in Turkey","datePublished":"2025-11-07T14:36:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:49:28+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/information-about-house-cleaning-and-expenses-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Information About House Cleaning and Expenses in Turkey","keywords":"House Cleaning","datePublished":"2025-11-07T14:36:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:49:28+03:00","articleSection":"Cost of Living and Accommodation","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Learn about house cleaning costs in Turkey. Get information now for professional cleaning services at affordable prices!","name":"Information About House Cleaning and Expenses in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/house-cleaning-and-expenses-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/house-cleaning-and-expenses-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/information-about-house-cleaning-and-expenses-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/house-cleaning-and-expenses-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Household cleaning in Turkey is more than just organizing the living space; it is the key to comfort, health and cultural harmony, especially for local and international students. In this article, you will discover the tricks, budget-friendly methods and cultural subtleties of house cleaning in Turkey. There are also practical tips for international students to help you easily adapt to your new life! A clean home means a peaceful life. Let&#8217;s start together!</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="house-cleaning-in-turkey-what-you-need-to-know-for-international-students">House Cleaning in Turkey: What You Need to Know for International Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When international students arrive in Turkey, they encounter many new experiences in both academic and social life. House cleaning is part of these experiences. Household cleaning in Turkey generally requires an organized and meticulous approach. Cleaning habits may vary due to cultural differences. For example, some families clean their homes frequently, while others may take a more flexible approach. Therefore, it is important to pay attention to local habits when cleaning the house.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="cleaning-habits">Cleaning Habits</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Cleaning habits in Turkey vary depending on the cultural background and lifestyle of families. Generally, household cleaning is done at <strong>least once a week</strong>. In addition, houses are often ventilated, especially in summer. Cleaning with these habits in mind can help students to better integrate with the local community.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="house-cleaning-costs-in-turkey-tips-for-planning-your-budget">House Cleaning Costs in Turkey: Tips for Planning Your Budget</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The cost of house cleaning varies in different cities in Turkey. In big cities like Istanbul, Ankara and Izmir, cleaning services are usually more expensive. However, if you prefer to clean on your own, you can significantly reduce these costs.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="cleaning-fees">Cleaning Fees</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Professional Cleaning Services:<br></strong>In Türkiye, professional cleaning services cost an average of $75 to $160. For example, cleaning a three-bedroom apartment costs approximately $60 to $100, while cleaning a duplex apartment costs around $100 to $160.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Cleaning Yourself:<br></strong>If you prefer to clean yourself, you should budget an average of $25 to $50 for the necessary supplies.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="tips-for-planning-your-budget">Tips for Planning Your Budget</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Buy Cleaning Supplies in Bulk:</strong> You can save money by buying cleaning supplies in bulk. Especially buying products such as detergents, sponges and cloths in large packages can reduce costs.</li>



<li><strong>Prefer Local Products:</strong> In Turkey, cleaning products from local brands are generally more affordable. You can balance your budget by choosing these products.</li>



<li><strong>Create a Cleaning Calendar:</strong> Scheduling house cleaning on a regular calendar makes things easier and helps you keep cleaning costs under control.</li>
</ul>



