"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/summer-rental-options-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/summer-rental-options-in-turkiye/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">With its stunning beaches, historic cities and cultural riches, Turkey is a popular destination for those looking for houses and rooms to rent during the summer season. While this high demand diversifies rental and subletting options for both local and foreign visitors, it also raises some confusing questions.<br>In this article, we take a closer look at how to find reliable summer rentals in Turkey, subletting opportunities, legal processes and tips on common issues.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="summer-rental-options-in-turkey-what-you-should-know">Summer Rental Options in Turkey: What You Should Know?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">During the summer months, Turkey sees an intense influx of tourism, especially in the coastal regions. For this reason, rental options are also quite diverse.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="types-of-rentals">Types of Rentals</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Short Term Rental</strong>: This type is usually preferred by vacationers and is rented on a daily or weekly basis. It is especially popular in the summer months.</li>



<li><strong>Long Term Rental</strong>: These are rentals for use outside of the summer, usually for 6 months or longer. It is an ideal option for students and employees.</li>



<li><strong>Summer Rental</strong>: Especially summer houses by the sea are among the most preferred accommodation options for vacationers.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When renting in the summer, it is important to consider factors such as location, price, and type of accommodation.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can also benefit from our article on <a title="Ways to Secure Accommodation in Turkey" href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Ways to Secure Accommodation in Turkey</a>.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="alt-kiralama-extra-income-opportunities-in-summer-in-turkey">Subletting: Extra Income Opportunities in Summer in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Subletting offers tenants the opportunity to rent out their rental property to others. This is an attractive option for those who want to earn additional income, especially during the summer period.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="sublease-advantages">Sublease Advantages</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Extra Income</strong>: You can earn additional income by renting out your rented house or apartment to others during the summer period.</li>



<li><strong>Cost Sharing</strong>: If you are going on a long-term trip during the summer months, subletting your property can reduce your costs.</li>



<li><strong>Flexibility</strong>: Subletting provides flexibility when you are not using your property during the vacation period.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-examples">Application Examples</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>If a student is going to stay with his family during the summer vacation, he can sub-let his rented apartment during the summer.</li>



