<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Summer rental prices vary depending on location and accommodation type. For example, the daily rent for an apartment in Istanbul can be between 12.5 &#8211; 37.5 USD, while in Bodrum it can be as high as 25 &#8211; 75 USD.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-should-i-pay-attention-to-when-subleasing">What should I pay attention to when subleasing?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When subletting, it is important to get the property owner&#8217;s permission and put the contract in writing. It is also helpful to clearly define the rights and responsibilities of tenants.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-documents-are-required-during-the-rental-process">What documents are required during the rental process?</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>The following documents are usually required during the rental process:</li>



<li>Certificate of identity</li>



<li>Rental agreement</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="which-platforms-can-i-use-for-short-term-rentals">Which platforms can I use for short-term rentals?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Popular platforms for short-term rentals include Airbnb, Booking.com and Sahibinden.com. These platforms offer various tools that facilitate the rental process.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-are-my-legal-rights-during-the-rental-process">What are my legal rights during the rental process?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">During the rental process, the tenant&#8217;s legal rights include safe use of the property, receiving services in accordance with the rental agreement, and recovering the deposit.</p>



